HEADWORD: Reflectent
<hw>Re*flect"ent</hw> <pr>(r?*fl?kt"<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>reflectens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>reflectere</ets>. See
<er>Reflect</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bending or flying back;
reflected.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The ray descendent, and the ray
<xex>reflectent</xex> flying with so great a speed.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir
K. Digby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Reflecting; <as>as, a <ex>reflectent</ex>
body</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir K. Digby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reflectible</ent>⟦br⟧
